  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Artificial Reef and Guardhouse &#x2013; coastal resource management/climate change resilience</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">- Capacitate the local fisherfolk association to design, fabricate, implement  and manage the appropriate Artificial Reef Project in the Tabugon marine protected area  
- Rehabilitate marine habitats by deploying 200 jackstone type artificial reefs in the MPA
- Protect the marine habitats by installing floating guardhouse managed by the deputized bantay dagat</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">- community consultation and inception meetings for the project
- planning and coordination with local government unit
- firming up and signing of partnership agreements
- procurement and purchase of materials
- construction and deployment of the ARs
-hand-over and evaluation</narrative>
  </description>
